		<!-- Marginalia -->
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="head">
					<marginalia_text>
						Nondum est in mundo vir: quia nulla est adhuc, qui tantu[m]
						facit, quantum potest vir.
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="pen" text="Nondum est in mundo vir:" type="straight"/>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						Cogitet quisq[uam], quanto plus posset,
						Si cogeretur extremas vires de improuiso extendere.
						Et quotidiè tantu[m] pra[e]stet pro virili:
						aut sanè non est vir.
						Is tandem
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						est vir, qui in dies Singulos quoquo modo distendit
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						suam virilem.
						Et ita
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="intext">
					<marginalia_text>
						semper dicit, facitq[ue], vt nec ipse, nec quisq[uam] hominu[m]
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="left_margin">
					<marginalia_text>
						possit meliùs.
						Pra[e]sertim in Causis magnis:
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
					<marginalia_text>
						aut apud illustres personas. Sed tame[n] quasi aliud agens.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				A true man in not yet found in the world, because until now there has been no man who does as much as a man can do.
				Every man would think about how much more he could do, if he were suddenly forced to extend his utmost abilities.
				And let him so excel daily, to the utmost of his ability, otherwise he indeed is not a man.
				However he is a man who every day stretches out his abilities in any way.
				Thus, he always speaks and acts, as if he himself or no other man could do better,
				especially in important matters or with illustrious people.
				However, he acts as if doing something else.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="IT">
				<position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
					<marginalia_text>
						( Pochi libri dell'antichi: mà molta pratica. )
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Few books from the ancients, but much practice.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
